    {
      "id": "572a56f2f330ec93407e956c0391d72ebe409730",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-12 06:57:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTo be honest, I do think Sarah has a good point, although this may not make the rest of the tests pass.  If the $CHECKSTAT gives unexpected results, it means something is wrong, and remounting the client is indeed a way to clean up for following tests.  However, looking at replay-single.sh, would we also want to remount the clients for the same reason after each $CHECKSTAT if unexpected results come up?  It seems to be going too far.\n\nAnother concern is that we might want to do the remount _after_ dumping logs, so that with smaller debug sizes, log lines are less likely to be lost.\n\nHmm, I'm not sure if I want a \"+1\" or \"-1\".  Adding Tappro here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
